  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hosting Senior Economic Justice Policy Advisor</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The build the capacity of civil society organisation to better analyse tax incentive policies, and advocate towards governments and international institutions on this issue of tax incentives - measured by greater awareness of CSO partners of this issue, and greater contact with policy makers and decision makers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to coordinate civil society voice towards governments and policy makers in both the global South and global North with regard to illicit financial flows that cause a loss of development financing.  The project seeks to adopt a human rights and gender equality as key lenses to analyse this problem, and focuses mainly on one aspect of illicit financial flows - namely the issue of tax incentives.   The staff member hosted &apos;senior economic justice policy advisor&apos; coordinates global work conducted within civil society with virtual and face-to-face meetings to establish common research basis and common advocacy and policy influencing strategies towards a diverse set of identified institutions and governments.</narrative>
  </description>
